gomodel:SYNGO_4065  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper uses high-resolution membrane capacitance (Cm) measurement combined with Ca2+-uncaging stimuli to monitor the effect of Unc31 KO in DCV exocytosis (as described in PMID:18031683).\n\nFigure 1A: Under Step-like elevations in intracellular calcium, membrane capacitance was significantly reduced in Unc31 mutant (unc-31e928) relative to WT indicating that Unc31 mutants defect exocytosis in ALA neurons of C. elegans. The exocytotic defect was fully rescued by reintroduction of full-length unc-31 cDNA.. Experimental description: The 3780-bp unc-31 cDNA (derived from PMID: 16272411) under the control of the rab-3 promoter was constructed for genetic rescue. The 1.2 kb rab-3 promoter was amplified by PCR and subcloned to pPD49.26 (1997 Fire Lab Vector Kit) to gain pPD49.26-Prab-3." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4065" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6239" .

